# Regression tests for GPU grouped matmul failures.
#
# Failures observed on a specific GPU platform:
#   - bf16, G=8,  wtag=abc, 64x64:8x64x64
#   - f16,  G=16, wtag=abc, 32x128:16x128x96
#   - f16,  G=16, wtag=acb, 32x128:16x128x96
#
# f32 and G=4 cases passed cleanly. Errors appear at column offsets >= 32,
# suggesting a 32-wide tile boundary or group-offset bug in the GPU kernel.
#
# Hypotheses under test:
#   H1  - bf16 group count threshold (G=4 passes, G=8 fails; find crossover)
#   H2  - bf16 at G=16 (currently untested at this count)
#   H3  - f16 group count threshold (G=8 passes, G=16 fails; find crossover)
#   H4  - layout sensitivity (abc vs acb at failing G counts)
#   H5  - N tile boundary (errors start at col >=32; does N<32 eliminate them?)
#   H6  - N scaling (does the bug worsen / shift with larger N?)
#   H7  - K scaling (does larger K matter independently of N?)
#   H8  - large group sizes with medium G
#   H9  - unbalanced / irregular group sizes at high G
#   H10 - very large G (32, 64)
#   H11 - f32 baseline at all failing shapes must pass

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# H11: f32 baseline -- all shapes below should pass; confirms reference is sane
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
--reset
--engine=gpu
--dt=f32:f32:f32
--wtag=abc,acb
--grouped=0:8:8,8,8,8,8,8,8,8
64x64:8x64x64
64x64:8x64x96
64x64:8x64x128
64x64:8x64x256
--grouped=0:16:2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2,2
32x128:16x128x96
32x128:16x128x128
--grouped=0:32:4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4,4
128x256:32x256x128

